Feature: Kubernetes startup orchestrator for local system bring-up

Contract IDs
- `CID-K8S-ORCH-STARTUP`
- `CID-K8S-ORCH-HEALTH`
- `CID-K8S-ORCH-ROLLOUT`

Functional requirements
- Add an orchestrator entrypoint under `k8infra` that can start the full local stack with one command.
- The orchestrator must cover the existing runbook flow from `k8infra/README-k8s-local.md`:
  - runtime + cluster checks/start (`colima`, `minikube`, ingress)
  - backend manifest apply (`k8infra/quarkus-backend.yaml`)
  - rollout/health verification in namespace `cinemas`
  - optional data seed hooks for `mysql_8/login.sql` and `mysql_8/book.sql`
- Startup order must be dependency-aware:
  - `mysql` first
  - then `dalogin`, `mbook`, `mbooks`, `simple-service-webapp`
  - verify readiness before moving to the next step
- Add orchestrator modes:
  - `up` (full startup)
  - `status` (pod/service/ingress health snapshot)
  - `restart <service>` (targeted rebuild/redeploy flow aligned with current image names)
  - `down` (controlled shutdown without deleting persistent volumes by default)
- The orchestrator output must be concise and deterministic for operator use (step banner, pass/fail state, next action on failure).
- Existing manual commands remain documented as fallback in `k8infra/README-k8s-local.md`.

Acceptance criteria
- A developer can bring up the stack from repo root with one orchestrator command and reach:
  - `https://milo.crabdance.com/login/`
  - `https://milo.crabdance.com/mbooks-1/rest/book/locations`
  - `https://milo.crabdance.com/simple-service-webapp/webapi/myresource`
- Orchestrator blocks on failed dependency readiness and exits non-zero with a clear failing step.
- `status` mode reports readiness for `mysql`, `dalogin`, `mbook`, `mbooks`, `simple-service-webapp`, and ingress endpoint reachability.
- `restart <service>` path performs only the service-scoped build/load/rollout path already used in the runbook.
- `k8infra/README-k8s-local.md` includes orchestrator usage and fallback/manual parity notes.

Definition of Done
- [ ] Spec + implementation + tested evidence present.
- [ ] `@testing-engineer` verification completed.
- [ ] `@security-specialist` verification completed.
- [ ] `@performance-engineer` verification completed.

